<DOC><DOCNO> ZF32-213-092 </DOCNO><DOCID>10 351 126</DOCID><JOURNAL>PC World  March 1991 v9 n3 p157(11).andM;</JOURNAL><TITLE>Can you do better than NetWare? (Software Review) (comparison offour network operating systems)(includes related article on makingpurchasing decisions) (evaluation)</TITLE><AUTHOR>Lauriston, Robert.andM;</AUTHOR><TEXT><ABSTRACT>Four network operating systems are reviewed and compared: NovellInc's Advanced NetWare SFT and NetWare 386 3.1, Microsoft Corp'sLAN Manager 2.0, and Banyan Systems' VINES.andP;  Reliability is themost important consideration when purchasing a server-basednetwork operating system (NOS); NetWare 386 is the most reliableof the four programs.andP;  LAN Manager uses 158Kbytes RAM and 4Mbytesof disk space on each workstation; there is not enough memory torun some applications, and serious bugs prevent some programs fromworking with the current version.andP;  Only OS/2 workstations canshare resources, and installation is extremely difficult.andP;  LANManager 2.0 is a poor value despite Microsoft's flexible pricingpolicy.andP;  NetWare 386 3.1 is rated a Best Buy.andP;  It is very easy toinstall and supports large amounts of RAM and disk space.andO;Advanced NetWare SFT is still an excellent choice for smallnetworks, but it is unreliable on large networks because of itspoor memory management.andP;  VINES 4.0 is easy to manage and has toolsfor multiple servers and WAN links but is very slow.andP;  A seriousdisadvantage is the fact that backup and restore operations mustbe run from the server.andM;</ABSTRACT></TEXT><DESCRIPT>Company:   Novell Inc. (Products)Microsoft Corp. (Products)Banyan Systems Inc. (Products).andO;Ticker:    MSFT; NOVL.andO;Product:   NetWare 386 3.1 (Network operating system)VINES (Network operating system)LAN Manager 2.0 (Network management software)NetWare SFT 2.15 (Computer network software).andO;Topic:     Local Area NetworksNetwork Operating SystemsEvaluation.andO;Feature:   illustrationtablegraph.andO;Caption:   What is RAM cram? (table)Features evaluation. (graph)Test report. (graph)andM;</DESCRIPT></DOC>